CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 8, 1956, pg. A2 reads: "Tax Program On WILY - John H. Bingler, director of the Bureau of Internal Revenue's office in Pittsburgh confers with Paul C. Pollard, revenue agent, who will be the main speaker on a program to answer questions of taxes which will be aired on WILY next year, while Herman C. Slanski, tax information agent, who will also be heard, along with Negro agents of the various departments of the local, looks on. The public will begin now to submit the questions to be answered. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of John H. Bingler, director of the Bureau of Internal Revenue's office in Pittsburgh; Paul C. Pollard, revenue agent, and Herman C. Slanski, tax information agent, gathered behind desk in interior to discuss WILY tax questions program
